princeton_ansible.title: Migrate libserv39 content to virtual infrastructure
Ensure Sanborn Map content is served up from lib-static.

comments.body:
The Sanborn maps seem to be in multiple places:
https://digitalsanbornmaps-proquest-com.ezproxy.princeton.edu/about?accountid=13314
https://library.princeton.edu/special-collections/divisions/historic-maps-collection
 https://maps.princeton.edu/?utf8=%E2%9C%93&search_field=all_fields&q=&featured=sanborn
We do plan to make a new landing page for this project to recreate the ability to explore the Sanborn maps in maps.princeton.edu that exists at https://library.princeton.edu/libraries/firestone/rbsc/aids/sanborn/sanborn-web.htm

We can also remove the `appdeploy` file in inventory.
And we can archive the Pulbot and Heaven repos.

If possible, add an [auto-reply in slack](https://slack.com/resources/using-slack/a-guide-to-slackbot-custom-responses), so when someone types `pulbot deploy` they get a reminder and a link to Ansible Tower.
